HEADWORD: duplicative
<hw>du"pli*ca*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the quality of duplicating or doubling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having the quality of subdividing
